<Author>kawh
<Content>A Very Pleasant Surprise! We got a great rate for this hotel-- and it was in the perfect location, just at the top of Ramblas-- so we didn't expect it to be great. We were pleasantly surprised. No Noise at all. We were in a room that had a window facing into a center solarium-ish opening. You could see other people's windows across the opening... but not a problem, as we kept our curtains shut. It was not far from the elevator... but was completely quiet. No noise at all. Very clean. Smallish bathroom. Good shower. Front desk was helpful when we needed it. Free wifi and also use of 1 computer near the front desk. (must stand to use the computer-- but this tends to limit people's time, so didn't usually have to wait.) Breakfast was slightly above average. fresh fruit. several choices of protein (soft and sliced cheese, ham, boiled eggs) several breads  cereals, fruit juice, toaster... it was quite a good selection. This is a short block off of Ramblas, at the top. Easy to walk down Ramblas or Passeig Gracia. Very near our favorite ice cream at Panelles Donat on the cute Portal de l'Angel. We liked this hotel for its location, cleanliness, and very quiet room. If noise is an issue, ask for a room around the solarium (i don't know what to call it... a space where 4 rooms face inward toward an empty space....??) -kawh 
