<Author>Chrystie22
<Content>Great Hotel...but a bit noisy! My sister and I stayed at the Atlantis from 3 to 6 June 2008 and had a great time. The hotel is ideally situated, 5mn from Placa de Catalunya where you can catch the Aerobus to the airport and Las Ramblas, a long street with many shops and restaurants. It is also close to all other attractions. Our room was nicely decorated and rather spacious, the only downside was that it was overlooking Carrer de Pelai, a very busy street, and the volume of noise was terrible! Moreover the windows were old and not closing properly so it was difficult to sleep but we somehow managed as we were tired after walking around town all day! The breakfast was quite good with a wide selection of food. All in all, a good experience and I would recommend it but I advise you to request a room overlooking the courtyard when you book if you want to have a good night sleep.... 
