<Author>SAFC08
<Content>Great hotel but noisy. We stayed 3 nights at the Atlantis in February and overall everything was great. Our junior suite on floor 3, was very spacious, clean and modern with a great bathroom and very comfortable beds. There was a great choice at breakfast ,staff were friendly and helpful and the breakfast room was clean and bright. The hotel's location is perfect, only 3 minutes walk to the top of Las Ramblas and there is a good range of shops, bars and restaurants nearby. There was however some problems with noise. A very noisy, foulmouthed American occupied the room next door on our 2nd night and woke us all at 6.00am when he returned drunk and started screaming and shouting.During our 3rd night, someone held a rave party in a nearby apartment and we were kept awake for 2 hours. The hotel concierge was apologetic and investigated but could not help. If you visit this hotel it might be worth checking if this problem is a regular occurence. Earplugs are recommended. 
