<Author>stokegifford
<Content>Atlantis Hotel..a nice experience. Atlantis Hotel. Barcelona SpainReviewer: A Trip Advisor member. Bristol UK.Stayed in the Atlantis between the 4th and 8th June 2007. A nice hotel, superbly situated at Pelai 20 some 150 metres from the start of the Rambla and central to just about everything you would wish for in a central Barcelona hotel. Had a double room on the top (5th) floor that was double glazed and therefore quiet with excellent air conditioning, comfortable beds and generally was in good decorative order.The breakfast was adequate with eggs, sausage bacon etc. as well as fresh and tinned fruits, meats, cheeses and cereals. The minor downside was that the toaster was not working but with only two female staff they were put under a lot of pressure especially when most of the guests decided on breakfast at the same time. All in all, a nice experience in this small but charming hotel. The reception staff were friendly and extremely helpful and I will be recommending it to my friends. 
